# Implementation Plan: Command Configuration Hub

Transform the placeholder Settings page into a functional control center for the Border Control station's operational preferences and identity.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The settings proposed here will be stored in `localStorage` for this browser session. In a full production environment, these would be synced to a backend `station_config` table. 

## Proposed Changes

### 🔧 [NEW] [SettingsContext](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/context/SettingsContext.jsx)
Implement a new React Context to manage global operational settings across the entire dashboard.
- **State**: `stationName`, `alertLevel`, `refreshInterval`, `enableNotifications`.
- **Persistence**: Auto-save and load from `localStorage`.

### 🎛️ [MODIFY] [Settings.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Settings.jsx)
Overhaul the UI to include:
- **Station Identity**: A text input to set the current Port of Entry name.
- **Operational Status**: A selector for the "Security Alert Level" (Normal, Elevated, High, Critical).
- **Communication Toggles**: Switches for the real-time alert dropdown and system sounds.

### 🏠 [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
- **Header Integration**: Display the "Current Station" name next to the "Command Overview" title.
- **Alert Level**: (Optional) Add a visual overlay or banner if the Alert Level is set to 'Critical'.

### 🔔 [MODIFY] [Header.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/components/Header.jsx)
- **Notification Respect**: Conditionally show the security alert bell based on the `enableNotifications` setting.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Change the **Station Name** and verify it updates on the Dashboard.
- Change the **Alert Level** and observe visual changes (e.g., status pill color).
- Toggle **Notifications** and verify the bell disappears/reappears.
- Refresh the page to ensure all settings persist in `localStorage`.
